This paper discusses the relationship between belief networks and relational databases, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method to construct belief networks automatically from statistical relational data, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also compares its method with other methods, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of its method, which could relate to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
